==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aquarius
<hw>A*qua"ri*us</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>aquarius</ets>, adj., relating to water, and n., a water-carrier,
fr. <ets>aqua</ets>. See <er>Aqua</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The Water-bearer; the eleventh sign in the zodiac,
which the sun enters about the 20th of January; -- so called from the
rains which prevail at that season in Italy and the East.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A constellation south of Pegasus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aquatic</ent>⟦br⟧
